pageContext.claim: “You know, we had probably -- and even the fake news would tell you -- the greatest victory in the history of this country in 2016. There's never been anything like that. The people came from the hills and the valleys. They came from all over. And they voted, voted, voted.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump lost the popular vote by about 3 million to Hillary Clinton. His 304 votes in the Electoral College were not a record.
